# Report Menu (`ReportMenu`)

**Path:** `src/app/components/ReportMenu.tsx`

Vertical list used on the **Reports** page to choose which report category to configure. Selection uses **Primary Weak** and **Surface Level 3** from `color/colors.mdc` (lighter than sidebar L2 for a softer in-page nav). **Do not** use a left accent bar or a different text colour for the active row—selection is shown by **background** and **font weight** only.

## Container (`<nav>`)

- `aria-label="Report types"`
- Layout: `flex flex-col gap-0.5 py-1 px-2`
- Horizontal `px-2` (8px) keeps rounded rows from clipping at the column edge while keeping label alignment consistent with the page title row (8px + 24px = 32px to label start when using `pl-6` on each row).

## Row (`<button type="button">`)

- Layout: `flex w-full items-center justify-between`
- Padding: `py-3 pl-6 pr-3`
- Radius: `rounded-[12px]` (same as L2 menu items)
- Transition: `transition-colors`

### Active (selected category)

- Background: `bg-[#e0f5fd]` — **Background Primary Weak** / sky_blue_50 (`color/colors.mdc`; lighter than `sky_blue_100` used in the main sidebar)
- Typography: `font-bold` on the button (label inherits)
- **No** left border / accent stripe
- **No** change to label or chevron colour vs inactive — both stay on the default palette below

### Inactive

- Weight: `font-medium`
- Hover: `hover:bg-[#fafafa]` — **Surface Level 3** (`var(--surface-level-3)`)

### Label

- Always: `text-[14px] leading-[24px] text-[#101010]` (active and inactive)

### Chevron

- Always: `size-4 shrink-0 text-[#7e7e7e]` (do not tint active blue)

## Data

- Categories live in `REPORT_CATEGORIES` (exported from this file for reuse or tests).
- Parent owns `selectedCategory` and passes `onSelectCategory(id)`.

## Integration

- Used inside `ReportsPage`: menu column flush to the main content left edge; vertical `#e0e0e0` divider and horizontal separators per `layout.mdc` / Reports layout spec.

