# Reports page — Please note (informational callout)

**Path:** `src/app/components/ReportsPage.tsx` (config panel, under the report-type title)

Inline notice before filters. Uses **notice / warning surface** tokens from `color/colors.mdc` without a coloured left stripe.

## Container

- `role="note"`
- Background: `bg-[#fff4e0]` (same warm surface as `DrawerBanner` warning in `RightDrawer.tsx`; pairs with Notice strong `#ff9d00` in the palette)
- Radius: `rounded-[8px]`
- Padding: `px-4 py-3`
- Optional max width: `max-w-[720px]` so long copy does not span the full config column
- **Do not** use `border-l-[3px]` or any **vertical accent bar** in this context—the drawer `DrawerBanner` warning may use a left border for emphasis in a drawer; the Reports inline callout does **not**.

## Content

- **Title:** `Please note` — `text-[14px] font-semibold text-[#101010] leading-[20px] mb-1`
- **Body:** `text-[14px] text-[#7e7e7e] leading-[24px]` (muted foreground per `typography.mdc`)

## Do not

- Do not use `border-l-[#004299]` or primary-coloured text for the active row.
- Do not use `bg-[#f5f9fe]` for active (that is table-row hover, not nav selection).

## Related rules

- `components/sidebar.mdc` — L1/L2 reference
- `components/right-drawer.mdc` — `DrawerBanner` warning (drawer context may keep `border-l-[3px]`; Reports inline callout does not)
- `interactions/interactions.mdc` — shared hover, focus, transition patterns
